<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-16T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-16T13:00:00-05:00" n="854" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d854">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 341.622a/132</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-16T18:00:00+00:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 16, 1916, 6 p. m.</hi>
                                </date>
                                <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.55 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4314. Your 3318, May 15, 12 noon, was communicated to <persName corresp="#p_GSE1">Sir Edward Grey</persName> to-day. He promised to
                            consult Mr. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName>, the First
                            Lord of the Admiralty, immediately and give an answer. He requested that
                            you be informed by telegraph meanwhile that the persons it is desired to
                            retain were known by the British authorities in the Orient at the time
                            of their seizure to have been incorporated in the armed forces of the
                            enemies of Great Britain, but that this knowledge had not reached him on
                            May 5 when he gave me his promise to release them.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>